   <img width=281 height=186
     src=bumbleb.jpg align=right hspace=20 alt="Bumble bee" border=3 v:shapes="_x0000_s1030">
   <![endif]>
   <b
     style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
     font-family:Papyrus'>Dr. <span
     class=SpellE>Jacek</span> <span class=SpellE>Radwan</span> (</span></b>
   <st1:place><st1:PlaceName><span
       class=SpellE><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
       style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>Jagiellonian</span></b></span></st1:PlaceName><b
      style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
      font-family:Papyrus'> </span></b><st1:PlaceType><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
       normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>University</span></b>
     </st1:PlaceType></st1:place>
   <b
     style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
     font-family:Papyrus'>, </span></b>
   <st1:place><st1:City><b
       style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
       font-family:Papyrus'>Krakow</span></b></st1:City><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
      normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>, </span></b><st1:country-region><b
       style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
       font-family:Papyrus'>Poland</span></b></st1:country-region></st1:place>
   <b
     style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
     font-family:Papyrus'>) has been awarded a 9 month <span class=SpellE>Fullbright</span>
    Fellowship (9 <span class=SpellE>mos</span>, from September 2000)
     to collaborate with me in a study of sexual selection in <span
     class=SpellE>acarid</span> mites. <span class=SpellE>Radwan</span> has
     been studying these mites since 1990. In several species of this family,
     two male morphs co-occur within the same populations: fighter males have a
     thickened and sharply terminated third pair of legs, whereas scramblers
     have unmodified legs. Modified legs are used during fights to stab (often
     mortally) other males. A males morph is determined in different ways
     (genetically or environmentally) in different species, and thus this
     system provides a unique opportunity to identify ecological factors
     favoring male dimorphism against <span class=SpellE>monomorphism</span>
    and those favoring environmental morph determination against genetic. The
    study will have two main objectives: 1. <span class=GramE>To</span>
    determine if individuals possessing phenotypes associated with lower
    fitness (scramblers) carry more deleterious mutations. 2. To determine
    whether superior metabolic competence and lower fluctuating asymmetry are
    associated with low mutational load and to resolve which of these measures
   is a better candidate for a general fitness index.<o:p></o:p></span></b></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
     auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
     normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>Hypoxia and
     larval care in the bumble
     bee, <span class=SpellE><em><span style='font-family:Papyrus'>Bombus</span></em></span><em><span
     style='font-family:Papyrus'> <span class=SpellE>occidentalis</span></span></em>
    (12 <span class=SpellE>mos</span>, from May 1996), </span></b>
   <st1:State><st1:place><b
       style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
       font-family:Papyrus'>Montana</span></b></st1:place></st1:State><b
     style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
     font-family:Papyrus'>'s NSF <span class=SpellE>EPSCoR</span> program. With
  Drs. P. <span class=SpellE>Kukuk</span> and D.L. Kilgore.<o:p></o:p></span></b></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
     auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
     normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>Courtship
     Energetics and the Heritability of Metabolic Competence (24 <span
     class=SpellE>mos</span>, from July 1994-96), National
     Science Foundation. Behavioral and respirometric
     research on the sierra dome spider <em><span style='font-family:Papyrus'>Linyphia
     litigiosa</span></em>.
  <o:p></o:p></span></b></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
     auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
     normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>REU supplement
     to support undergraduate summer research relating rates of aging to sexual
     competitiveness in the sierra dome spider (6 <span class=SpellE>mos</span>),
     NSF.
  <o:p></o:p></span></b></li>
</ul>

