  <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
      auto;mso-list:l10 level2 lfo15;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><strong><span
      style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>Multi-week zero-benefit
      guarding of aphid colonies by carpenter <a
      href="http://es.rice.edu/projects/Bios321/eusocial.insect.html">ants</a>:
      slave-making aphids or investing <a
      href="http://members.aol.com/dinarda/ant/index.htm">ants</a>?</span></strong>
    <st1:State><st1:place>
        </st1:place></st1:State>
  </li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
      auto;mso-list:l10 level2 lfo15;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><strong><span
      style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>The effects of operational
      sex ratio and female hunger on mating propensity and duration in three
      water strider species (</span></strong><em><b><span style='font-size:
      13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>Aquarius <span class=SpellE>remigis</span>, <span
      class=SpellE>Gerris</span> <span class=SpellE>buenoi</span>, G. <span
      class=SpellE>incurvatus</span></span></b></em><strong><span
      style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>).</span></strong><b
      style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
      font-family:Papyrus'> Collaborating with undergraduates from my summer
    field courses.<o:p></o:p></span></b></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
      auto;mso-list:l10 level2 lfo15;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><strong><span
      style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>A Darwinian critique of
      psychotherapeutic intervention strategies</span></strong><b
      style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
      font-family:Papyrus'>. I continue research for a book
      aimed at evaluation of treatment methods used in a spectrum of
    psychotherapeutic traditions</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
      font-family:Papyrus'><span class="style5">.
    <o:p></o:p>
    </span></span><span class="style10">I would love to find a coauthor.</span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
      auto;mso-list:l10 level2 lfo15;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><strong><span
      style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>Development of methods to
      quantify levels of <a
      href="http://www.biology.ualberta.ca/palmer.hp/asym/asymmetry.htm">fluctuating
      asymmetry</a></span></strong><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
      style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'> using <a
      href="http://life.bio.sunysb.edu/morph">morphometric programs</a> based
    on thin plate <span class=SpellE>splines</span> relative warp analysis.<o:p></o:p></span></b></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
      auto;mso-list:l10 level2 lfo15;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><strong><span
      style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Papyrus'>Nutrition, re-mating
      propensity and contingent female sexual preferences in <span
      class=SpellE><span class=GramE>mormon</span></span> crickets</span></strong><b
      style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
      font-family:Papyrus'>. Field and laboratory study conducted by my <a
      href="http://biology.unm.edu/Biology/pwatson/public_html/ab.htm">Animal
    Behavior field course</a> from 1994-2000.</span></b><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
       id="_x0000_s1034" type="#_x0000_t75" alt="Mormon cricket" style='position:absolute;
       left:0;text-align:left;margin-left:6204.25pt;margin-top:0;width:309.75pt;
